juvenile court.
SB296 INTRODUCED
197 (f) After a volunteer advocate has been appointed to a
198 case by a juvenile court, notice of all juvenile court
199 hearings and reviews in that case shall be provided to the
200 local volunteer advocate program in the same manner as notice
201 is provided to attorneys and parties in the case. This notice
202 shall continue for the duration of the volunteer advocate's
203 appointment in the case, unless the appointment is terminated
204 or modified by order of the juvenile court.
205 (g) A volunteer advocate appointed pursuant to this
206 section shall be subject to the provisions of The Volunteer
207 Service Act in Section 6-5-336, including Section 6-5-336(d)
208 providing for immunity from civil liability in any action.
209 (h) The state entity shall continue to provide this
210 support service to existing and any future local volunteer
211 advocate programs.
212 (i) The state entity shall develop minimum standards
213 for local volunteer advocate programs, which shall include,
214 but not be limited to, standards relating to ethical conduct
215 and confidentiality, governance, employee management,
216 volunteer management, and data collection.
217 (j) The state entity shall develop in-service training
218 curricula for initial and continuing education of volunteer
219 advocates covering topics and matters that would assist
220 volunteer advocates who are appointed by juvenile courts to
221 advocate for the best interests of children.
222 (k) All existing and future local volunteer advocate
223 programs shall satisfy all of the following:
224 (1) Be members of the state entity as provided in
