225 subsection (l).
226 (2) Be responsible for the full range of volunteer
227 advocate management duties, including, but not limited to, the
228 recruitment, screening, training, support, and supervision of
229 volunteer advocates.
230 (3) Ensure that volunteer advocates, governing board
231 members, and employees comply with all policies, plans,
232 procedures, and requirements established by both the state
233 entity and the local volunteer advocate program.
234 (4) Conduct in-service training for the initial and
235 continuing education of volunteer advocates, in accordance
236 with the curricula specified in subsection (j).
237 (5) Ensure the proper management and accountability of
238 all local volunteer advocate program funding.
239 (l) In order to be eligible for full membership in the
240 state entity, a current or future local volunteer advocate
241 program shall do all of the following:
242 (1) Operate as a nonprofit corporation under the
243 requirements of the Alabama Nonprofit Corporation Law, Chapter
244 3 of Title 10A.
245 (2) Enter into a membership agreement with the state
246 entity.
247 (3) Have an executive director. Umbrella programs are
248 allowed only if they were in existence on the effective date
249 of this act, and these programs shall designate an individual
250 to oversee the local volunteer advocate program.
251 (4) Provide assurance that the executive director, or
252 other individual overseeing the local volunteer advocate
